<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78766458-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s80a–57"><num value="80a–57">§ 80a–57.</num><heading> Changes in investment policy</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">No business development company shall, unless authorized by the vote of a majority of its outstanding voting securities or partnership interests, change the nature of its business so as to cease to be, or to withdraw its election as, a business development company.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78766459-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/act/1940-08-22/ch686">Aug. 22, 1940, ch. 686</ref>, title I, § 58, as added <ref href="/us/pl/96/477/tI/s105">Pub. L. 96–477, title I, § 105</ref>, <date date="1980-10-21">Oct. 21, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2285">94 Stat. 2285</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
